desc: A dynamic programing language used for mainly for web development. Scripting with JavaScript allows developers to manipulate the DOM dynamically. The versitile language is used in browsers and on the backend with NodeJS.
experience: JavaScript is the programing language I am most experienced in. I have created many projects using this powerful language from static pages to full stack applications. Used along with powerful technologies like NextJS, TypeScript, and a seemingly endless resevoir of open source libraries making complicated web aplications is quick and painless.
name: JavaScript

desc: TypeScript is a syntactic superset of JavaScript that adds static typing to the language. It helps developers write more robust code by strictly typing variables, objects, functions, etc. TypeScript will warn you of possible bugs before its compiled into JavaScript.
experience: I have been taking advantage of TypeScript in all of my most recent JavaScript projects. The intellisence that comes along with using TypeScript makes developing code much more streamlined especially when using new libraries as it works as documention.
name: TypeScript

desc: Python is a dynamic programing language. Versitile, it can be used for an array of soltions such as creating programs, web development, data science, and machine learning to name a few. Python's intuitive syntax makes it quick to write and reads like plain english.
experience: I have a basic knowlege of Python. I am familiar with the syntax and have used it to make a basic rest server using Flask. I am currently looking into machine learning using python and tensorflow.
name: Python

desc: C# is an object-oriented and component-oriented typed programming language. It runs in the .NET framework which includes a vast selection of methods and libraries to take advantage of in your codebase.
experience: I have a basic knowlege of C# and have been learning more in my free time. Mainly messing around with game development in the Unity engine but also spending a little time looking into ASP.NET. I would love an oppertunity to create a desktop program or website so I can take a deeper dive into C#.
name: C#

desc: PHP is a server-side scripting language. It is used in web development and is able to be embeded in the HTML of a website. PHP is widely used throughout the web. While newer technologies have come into the space, PHP is still the leader in server-side languages for websites. This is due to Facebook and the ease of use of the CMS WordPress which makes getting a basic website out on the web quick and easy.
experience: I have a basic understanding of PHP mainly from maintaining legacy code at work. I have worked with the microframework Lumen to maintain a RESTful api. I find PHP fairly simple to use. I would like an oppertunity to create a website from scratch using PHP to expand my proficiency with this language in the future. While it may not be used as widely in large newer projects, it is a dominant player in the legacy code space and it certainly a good technology to know.
name: PHP
